column5: They will not accept a Rapid antigen test. ID Now is a rapid diagnostic test. It's processed in-house not sent off to a lab. It's an NAAT test.

The accepted pre-entry test list includes a isothermal amplification test. The ID Now test uses that technology according to documentation from the Walgreens site. If anyone has had any issue with this test being accepted, please let us know. I'll get mine on September 8!

Trout, I am right next to you in Dayton and my friend from Champlin are heading up September 4th. May I ask where you got your test as I inquired at the Walgreens on 169 and did not get a very good answer from them. I have time to research but your post seemed like a great place to start!
I went in and talked to the Pharmacist at the one on Rockford road in Plymouth. They have the quick test that is allowed by Canada.
Dave, Did you plan your trip yet? Paul

Walgreens does the Nucleic with a 2 hour turnaround time. These tests are considered acceptable molecular tests: * PCR - Polymerase chain reaction * RT-PCR Ã¢Â€Â“ reverse transcription real time PCR * Quantitative PCR (qPCR) - [x] Nucleic acid test (NAT) or Nucleic acid amplification test (NAATs) * Reverse transcription loop-mediated isothermal amplification (RT-LAMP) * Isothermal amplification * Droplet digital PCR or digital droplet PCR (ddPCR) * Transcription-mediated amplification (TMA) * RNA (Ribonucleic acid) * Ct (cycle threshold) * CRISPR * Sequencing * Next generational sequencing (NGS) or whole genome sequencing (WGS) * Oxford Nanopore sequencing (LamPORE) * Detection of the N gene * Detection of Orf1a/b * Detection of the S gene * Detection of the E gene * Detection of the RdRp gene Antigen not accepted.
The ID Now test is the type which is on the list of approved tests. Get one if you can.

We just got back from a quick trip to Sioux Lookout last weekend and they accepted our ID Now Walgreens tests for all 3 of us. I wasn't really concerned as it was on their list, but you never know I guess. Side note, only took about 45 minutes to get the results emailed to us. As long as you have all your information filled out in the app etc you will be good to go. Safe travels all.
What test did you take? From ?
Just a molecular test from a hospital which I believe are shipped to texas and normally 24-48 hr. Naat were not available anymore in my area.
Hope for the best. Good luck!

I did the Walgreens ID now test and it is a NAAT test. I got my results in a hour. I printed out the results and I just have to do the ArriveCan and I'm good to go. Good luck to all.

No place to upload the test actually, I just handed him our vaccine cards and print outs of the test PDF when he asked. I've heard digital works as well, but the print outs worked well for us.
